SCP-746: Honestly, I had my years of fun and I'm happy to have it end with the pleasure of fooling an oni. As said in English: [Speaks in English] Out with a bang.
附加记录：    

I love this sort of quirkiness, and I feel like it definitely mirrors how in Asian cultures (from my experience, anyway) people like to sprinkle in words from other Western languages from time to time. English is common, but I've also been in conversations where French phrases were tossed in too.

+1 from me, good bird friend

Also this is totally unrelated, but I was almost getting vibes of Chef Motokichi Yukimura (video about him teaching a guy how to make his signature omelette rice here: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=rFAddL8g8mw) while reading, and that just made me super happy. Cheery people who love what they do and make other people cheery are the best.





